1. Clean code should be elegant - simple and clean, no redandency
2. Clean code should be focued - each function, each class should conecentrate on addressing one problem, the logic is clear
3. Clean code needs to be well maintained, probably needs to take time to organise it.
4. Consider all the edge cases and pass all the tests.
5. No duplications in the code
6. Meaningful names - a strict rule in naming a variable, a function and a class. And the name needs to make sense for the reader.
7. Exception handling - should be able to handle different errors
8. Comments - only when necessary
9. 
